        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName><sic>Pittsburg</sic></placeName> <date>Sept. 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p>Dear Sir&#33;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Since so much has been said<lb/> and as I find even <sic>falshoods</sic>&#44; by some<lb/> slanderous tongues&#44; about the polish Con&#45;<lb/>gregation&#44; as once remarked in your columns<lb/> as still existing in the members at their last<lb/> meeting wished me as their Sec&#39;y to<lb/> make you <sic>aquainted</sic> with the present<lb/> position of the <add>Hebrew</add> called <add>Hebrew</add>.<lb/> We consist of twelve actual members<lb/> and have a synagogue with Sepher<lb/> and all other necessities&#44; where we have<lb/> met <date>Rosh Hashanah</date> &#38; <date>Jom Kipur</date><lb/> and besides electing at our last meeting<lb/> <persName>Mr. N. Eisendrath</persName> Parnass <persName>Mr. L. Juteur</persName><lb/> Treas. &#38; <persName>L. Jaroslawski</persName> Sec. we have<lb/> also elected <persName>Mr M. Marcussohn</persName> who<lb/> was on his journey to <placeName>Cleveland</placeName>&#44; and<lb/> visited our place of worship during his<lb/> stay over <date>Jom Kipur</date>&#44; as our <hi rend="underline">chasan</hi><lb/> and Shochet&#44; and Mohul. We would<lb/> thank you very much for the benefit of<lb/> the readers of your valuable paper</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>to mention these facts in your next<lb/> number. We hope and trust with the<lb/> <sic>assistence</sic> of the <persName>Rev. Mr. Marcusson</persName><lb/> as our spiritual guide&#44; that we will<lb/> prosper&#44; and continue to exist for the<lb/> benefit of the rising generation&#44; and for<lb/> the diffusion of the principles of Judaismus<lb/> and the God of <placeName>Israel</placeName> will grant us his<lb/> blessing.</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Yours very Respectfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Leopold Jaroslawski</persName></p>
			<p>The above letter I wrote to comply with your wish<lb/> expressed in your <date>May</date> number&#44; we also wish to<lb/> remark&#44; that we fully cherish your sentiments<lb/> of yours from <date>September</date>&#44; as nothing ever has<lb/> been said or done by either of our party<lb/> to prove injurious to our faith&#44; and vindi&#45;<lb/>cate our actions&#44; since you will be well<lb/> aware that it is not difficult to misre&#45;<lb/>present any one behind his back.<lb/> I am though fully convinced&#44; that no<lb/> <sic>falshood</sic> could prejudice your sound<lb/> judgment.</p>
          
        </body>
